You are writing the AGENT layer. Agents are stateless async workers that consume domain models and produce domain models.

## Mandatory agent contract
- MUST extend `BaseAgent` from `backend/agents/base_agent.py`
- MUST implement `async def run(self, input: BaseEntity) -> BaseEntity`
- MUST implement `def validate_input(self, input: BaseEntity) -> bool`
- MUST set `agent_name: ClassVar[str]` as a class variable
- MUST return a fully typed domain model, NEVER a raw dict or string
- MUST populate `reasoning_trace` on every model returned

## LLM call rules
- All LLM calls via `self._llm` injected at construction, never instantiated inside run()
- Wrap every LLM call: `async with self._timed_call("task_name"):` for automatic timing
- Max iterations per task: 3 tool call loops — add a counter and break if exceeded
- On any LLM failure: catch exception, log it, return a degraded domain model with `confidence_score=0.0`
- Never let an agent raise an exception to its caller

## Parallel execution (LangGraph)
- enrichment, intent_scorer, persona_agent MUST run via `Send()` — never sequential
- Each parallel agent writes to its own state key — no shared mutable state
- Use `Annotated[list, operator.add]` for any field multiple agents append to

## Forbidden in agents/
- No FastAPI imports, no response schemas
- No direct database calls
- No hardcoded model names — read from `settings.MODEL_NAME`
- No `time.sleep` — use `asyncio.sleep` if needed
